Parents and Guardians,

COVID-19 UPDATE: The Corinth School District was notified today of one student at Corinth Elementary School testing positive for COVID-19. This student had not been present since the second week of school so no one was quarantined.

The state does not require Mississippi schools to inform the public when teachers and students test positive for COVID-19. The CSD has made the decision to continue to keep reporting this information to you. Please keep in mind that other schools not making public announcements doesn‚Äôt mean they don‚Äôt have positive cases.

The District remains in contact with the Mississippi State Department of Health and the Centers for Disease Control to help ensure that we are creating as safe a learning environment as possible.

Release: 8/21/2020
text:

PreK and Kindergarten - Tuesday, July 21

Distribution of Senior Caps and Gowns

Seniors will pick up graduation caps and gowns on Wednesday, May 27th and Thursday, May 28th, from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m., in the front of CHS. Seniors will need to bring their computer, charged and cleaned, with charger, long cord, and cube. All school property, including cleaned out backpacks, calculators textbooks, and athletic gear, etc. should be turned in at this time.

A tent will be set up at the front of the school to allow for drive thru drop-off and pick-up. All fines (lunch, athletic, lab, etc.) must be paid to receive your cap and gown.

Corinth High School Graduation Ceremony Plans
A committee composed of student council officers, class officers, school administrators, and parent representatives met on multiple occasions to consider Graduation Ceremony Plans for the Corinth High School graduating class of 2020. These recommendations were presented to the Corinth School District Board of Trustees for their consideration at its regular meeting on May 14, 2020.

post_text:
DON'T FORGET!! Packet pick up TOMORROW!!
The Corinth School District will distribute additional learning packets for the remainder of the school year. These packets will be distributed at Corinth Elementary and Corinth Middle Schools on Saturday, April 18, 2020, from 11:00-2:00.

All packets will be distributed through the carlines. Please stay in your car and staff will bring the packets to you.

All Pre-K and Kindergarten children need to pick-up a packet. Packets will be available for all grades PreK-8 with the exception of Grade 4. Students in Grade 4 have the plans and information they need for the remainder of the year.

Packets for Speech students have been prepared and need to be picked up.

Students in grades 1-8 who have on-line access do not need to pick-up a packet. However, if you want one, please feel free to pick one up.

Thank you for partnering with Corinth School District teachers in providing learning opportunities for your children.

CES & CMS Additional Opportunity
for Device and Material Pick Up
An additional pick-up opportunity will be held for those parents who have not able to pick-up
materials or devices from Corinth Elementary or Middle Schools. This opportunity will be Wednesday, March 25, 2020, from 8:00 -10:00.
This will be a drive-through process and everyone should enter through the car line entrance.
All materials and devices will be delivered to your car.
School Staff will guide each vehicle through the line and process. Parents/students should not
leave their cars and will not be allowed to enter the building.
A parent must be present for a device to be checked out. In an effort to expedite delivery,
please do not sign-out a device for home if your child already has computer access at home.

post_text:
CORINTH SCHOOL DISTRICT
COVID 19 Statement #5
CAMBRIDGE AICE EXAMS CANCELED
MARCH 24, 2020
The Covid-19 outbreak is changing rapidly in countries around the globe, including and especially in the United States. Many countries have decided to extend school closures into May and June, making it impossible to hold examinations. Cambridge has made the difficult decision not to administer the international paper-based examinations in the May/June 2020 series in schools in any country.

All certificates from Cambridge International, including the Cambridge AICE Diploma, will be awarded to qualified candidates. Every entry for the May/June series will receive a grade, and if they have fulfilled the requirements, students can still receive the Cambridge AICE Diploma. Cambridge will release further guidance on how students will receive these grades later this week.

The Corinth School District will share this information as soon as Cambridge makes it available.

post_text:
If you are experiencing time zone difficulties on your device, We've had some success with asking students to power off their devices, restart (charged), and give the computer a few minutes to update- not always, but a troubleshooting method we wanted to share! **UPDATE:
1. if the power off then power back up does not re-set the date/stamp, here is another work around

control/shift/option/power all at the same time, hold down approx 20 sec. then restart computer.

2. Also for Secondary, if Parent Controls seem to be enabled with using Safari, use/default to Google Chrome. For Youtube, Google Chrome should be used. #DistanceLearningCSD

post_text:
JOIN US TONIGHT AT CHS in the auditorium for information about the ESSA Waiver Application process. This meeting will be at 6 p.m.

The Corinth School District is committed to improving our
schools and providing a high-quality education for your
children. As you are aware, as part of our District of
Innovation status, the Corinth School District has
implemented the Cambridge Assessment International
Program. Our students have achieved success in this
program and on the associated course examinations.

The Corinth School District will be submitting a waiver
request to the Mississippi Department of Education and the
U. S. Department of Education to allow us to substitute
selected Cambridge examinations in lieu of the required
Mississippi high school assessments. We would like to
share information with you about our request and give you
a meaningful opportunity to provide input in this process.
text:
JOIN US TONIGHT AT CHS in the auditorium for information about the ESSA Waiver Application process. This meeting will be at 6 p.m.

The Corinth School District is committed to improving our
schools and providing a high-quality education for your
children. As you are aware, as part of our District of
Innovation status, the Corinth School District has
implemented the Cambridge Assessment International
Program. Our students have achieved success in this
program and on the associated course examinations.

The Corinth School District will be submitting a waiver
request to the Mississippi Department of Education and the
U. S. Department of Education to allow us to substitute
selected Cambridge examinations in lieu of the required
Mississippi high school assessments. We would like to

post_text:
This morning Corinth High School administrators received a report that a student had a weapon. The administrators immediately detained the student and contacted the Corinth Police Department. A search of the student revealed he did have a concealed weapon. The Corinth Police Department took custody of the student and transported him to the Corinth Police Department.

Corinth High School administrators and the Corinth Police Department are to be commended for their prompt and professional response to the situation. The Corinth Police Department is now in charge of the investigation.

The Corinth School District is committed to providing safe and orderly schools for all of our children.
